# Instructions for Runtime Configuration:
# 
# This app now supports runtime configuration! Environment variables are loaded in this order:
# 1. Runtime environment variables (highest priority)
# 2. .env.local (local overrides, gitignored)
# 3. .env.{NODE_ENV} (environment-specific: .env.development, .env.production, etc.)
# 4. .env (base configuration)
#
# Quick Setup Options:
#
# Option 1 - Use environment-specific templates (RECOMMENDED):
#   cp .env.development.template .env.development     # For development
#   cp .env.staging.template .env.staging             # For staging
#   cp .env.production.template .env.production       # For production
#   # Edit the files with your sensitive values (Client ID, etc.)
#
# Option 2 - Use this general template:
#   cp env.example .env.development     # For development
#   cp env.example .env.production      # For production
#   # Edit the files with your values
#
# Option 3 - Local override file:
#   cp env.example .env.local           # For any environment (gitignored)
#   # Edit with your values
#
# Option 4 - Runtime environment variables:
#   export VITE_ADOBE_CLIENT_ID=your-value
#   export VITE_BUCKET=your-value
#   npm run build:prod
#
# The build process automatically generates dist/config.js with the resolved values.
# Runtime env vars take priority over .env files.
#
# Environment Template Files Available:
# - .env.development.template (contains dev-specific config, safe to commit)
# - .env.staging.template (contains staging-specific config, safe to commit)
# - .env.production.template (contains prod-specific config, safe to commit)
#
# Environment variables currently used in the codebase:
# - VITE_ADOBE_CLIENT_ID (used in AdobeSignInButton.tsx)
# - VITE_BUCKET (used in MainApp.tsx)
# - VITE_RIGHTS_AUTH_API_URL (used in FadelApiClient)
# - VITE_RIGHTS_AUTH_API_TOKEN (used in FadelApiClient)
# - VITE_FADEL_ASSET_DETAILS_API_URL (used in FadelApiClient)
# - VITE_FADEL_AGREEMENT_DETAIL_API_URL (used in FadelApiClient)
# - VITE_TCCC_FADEL_CUSTOMER_NAME (used in FadelApiClient)
# - VITE_TCCC_FADEL_CONNECTOR_VERSION (used in FadelApiClient)
# - VITE_TCCC_FADEL_DOMAIN_NAME (used in FadelApiClient)
